'''''Gertrude's Puzzles''''' is a 1984 [[edutainment]] [[video game]] for the [[Apple II]], [[Commodore 64]], and [[IBM PC compatible]]s by [[The Learning Company]].<ref>{{cite book |title=Gertrude's Puzzles - User's Manual |date=1982 |publisher=The Learning Company |url=ftp://ftp.apple.asimov.net/pub/apple_II/documentation/applications/misc/Gertrude's%20Puzzles%20manual.pdf}}</ref> It is considered a sequel to the game ''[[Gertrude's Secrets]]''. ''Gertrude's Puzzles'' was designed by [[Teri Perl]].<ref>{{cite book |title=Gertrude's Puzzles - User's Manual |date=1982 |publisher=The Learning Company |url=ftp://ftp.apple.asimov.net/pub/apple_II/documentation/applications/misc/Gertrude's%20Puzzles%20manual.pdf}}</ref> ''Gertrude's Puzzles'', like ''Gertrude's Secrets'', consists of a series of rooms,<ref>{{cite web |title=Gertrude's Puzzles |url=http://education.miami.edu/BlantonW/5dClhse/artifacts/task_cards/pdf/brain_gyms/gertrudes_puzzles.pdf |website=University of Miami |access-date=7 December 2018}}</ref> each of which contains a logic or categorization puzzle to solve using shapes and colors.

